Originally (along with a top-hat and walking-cane), Etonian dress was reserved for formal occasions, but boys wear it today for classes, which are referred to as <a3_0>"divisions", or "divs"<a3_0/>. As stated above, King's Scholars wear a <b7_0><b8_0>black<b8_0/><b7_0/> gown over the top of their tailcoats, and occasionally a surplice in Chapel. <a1_0>Members of the teaching staff<a1_0/> (known as <b6_0>Beaks<b6_0/>) are required to wear a form of school dress <a2_0>when teaching<a2_0/>.
